# YOLO Commands: Allowlist / Denylist

## ✅ Allowed
- `uv run pytest`
- `uv run black .`
- `uv run ruff .`
- `uv run mypy .`
- `git status`
- `mkdir`
- `tree`
- `echo`
- `cat`
- `cp`
- `mv`
- `curl`
- `python -m ...`

## ❌ Forbidden
- `rm` (any form)
- `git push`
- `wget`
- `systemctl`
- plain `pip install` (must use `uv pip install` if explicitly approved)

## Notes
- Only safe, read-only, or formatting commands may be auto-run.
- Test commands (`pytest`, `ruff`, `mypy`) must always run via `uv run`.
- New external packages: require explicit approval and `uv pip install`.